{
  "stem": "7458.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The Germans were using paratroopers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They would drop paratroopers in back of the front, surround a whole army, and liquidate them or capture them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And before you know it, we could see Russian soldiers running around in total disarray, in total confusion, not knowing what was going on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They kept assuring us that, oh, we'll-- we'll fight the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We'll drive them out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But we knew that things were bad.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And it was just one week later after hostilities began, again on the weekend, that the Germans marched into Jasionowka.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And this time, they were not so nice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The night that they marched into Jasionowka, we heard rumors, even before, that wherever they marched in, they burned, they killed, they raped, and they did horrible things to the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So as we knew that they were coming in, my family, living on the outskirts of town, we ran to the woods to hide.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Those who did not run, the Germans, with the help of the Polish people-- our neighbors-- rounded up on that day.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They drove everybody to the center of town and lined them up against the church wall.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They set up machine guns ready to machine gun everybody.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "They stood there for hours lined up in the center of town, when, evidently-- I was not there, but evidently-- a high German officer drove by.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And he said-- he made a little speech to the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And he said, we could shoot you all right now, but that would be an easy death.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "We don't want you to die so easily.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "We want you to slave for us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We want you to work for us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "We want to take every penny you've got, every ounce of strength.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
